
'''= a project to build a series  of calculators to 'map' the public domain in different jurisdictions, by  showing which works are out of copyright'''

URL = http://okfn.org/wiki/PublicDomainCalculators


=Status=

November 2008:

"There are now individuals and 
groups keen to contribute to the calculators in over 10 countries, 
including: Argentina, Belgium, Canada, Chile, Italy, Norway, 
Philippines, Sweden, Switzerland, United Kingdom, United States.

Ultimately we'd like to see the formation of loose-knit groups to 
create, maintain and review charts representing relevant legislation in 
different countries. These charts would be converted into code, and 
combined with metadata about works to give a sense of what works are in 
the public domain in each jurisdiction.

At the 3rd COMMUNIA Workshop in Amsterdam the OKF gave a presentation on 
the project, and there is now a new COMMUNIA Working Group, which will 
include work on the calculators across Europe!

We've set up a mailing list for interested parties to discuss 
developments and to share experience in creating flow charts to 
represent the law. If you know someone who might be interested in 
getting involved, please drop us a line!

